array.string: Lalala these topics are really simple. You just need to spend some time to understand them and they would appear to be common sense.
The geometry taught in sec 1 and sec 2 is pretty simple. It is basically just about shapes, sizes, and relations (how two figures relate to each other).
Algebra is not that hard. It doesn't require much memorising. To be good at algebra you just need to understand some of the concepts.
They don't teach much about statstics in secdonary school. And that makes statstics a giveaway in exams.
Set theory is a branch of maths that studies "collections of objects". You just have to understand the notations used in set theory and it would be a giveaway in exams.
Trigonometry evloved from geometry. Unlike geometry, trigonometry only focuses on triangle. And that is because triangles are cool.
Despite the fact that this is called "high-level calculation", they are just simple things. Take some time to learn them, and you would realize how easy they are.
This is a slightly advanced topic in algebra. They may look complicated and confusing at the start, but they are indeed some simple and elegant things.
Now, geometry starts to get interesting. But it is still very easy.
Calculus is basically a branch of maths that studies continuously changing quantities. Calculus may look very complicated at the start but it is acutally very easy.
